                 "said, 'The fire of God has fallen from the sky, and has "
                 "burned up the sheep and the servants, and consumed them, and "
                 "I alone have escaped to tell you.'\n"
                 "While he was still speaking, there came also another, and "
                 "said, 'The Chaldeans made three bands, and swept down on the "
                 "camels, and have taken them away, yes, and killed the "
                 "servants with the edge of the sword; and I alone have "
                 "escaped to tell you.'\n"
                 "While he was still speaking, there came also another, and "
                 "said, 'Your sons and your daughters were eating and drinking "
                 "wine in their oldest brother's house,\n"
                 "and behold, there came a great wind from the wilderness, and "
                 "struck the four corners of the house, and it fell on the "
                 "young men, and they are dead. I alone have escaped to tell "
                 "you.'\n"
                 "Then Job arose, and tore his robe, and shaved his head, and "
                 "fell down on the ground, and worshiped.\n"
                 "He said, 'Naked I came out of my mother's womb, and naked "
                 "shall I return there. Yahweh gave, and Yahweh has taken "
                 "away. Blessed be Yahweh's name.'\n"
                 "In all this, Job did not sin, nor charge God with "
                 "wrongdoing.\n"
                 "Then Job answered Yahweh,\n"
                 "'I know that you can do all things,\n"
                 "and that no purpose of yours can be restrained.\n"
                 "You asked, 'Who is this who hides counsel without "
                 "knowledge?'\n"
                 "therefore I have uttered that which I did not understand,\n"
                 "things too wonderful for me, which I didn't know.\n"
                 "You said, 'Listen, now, and I will speak;\n"
                 "I will question you, and you will answer me.'\n"
                 "I had heard of you by the hearing of the ear,\n"
                 "but now my eye sees you.\n"
                 "Therefore I abhor myself,\n"
                 "and repent in dust and ashes.'\n"
                 "It was so, that after Yahweh had spoken these words to Job, "
                 "Yahweh said to Eliphaz the Temanite, 'My wrath is kindled "
                 "against you, and against your two friends; for you have not "
                 "spoken of me the thing that is right, as my servant Job "
                 "has.\n"
                 "Now therefore, take to yourselves seven bulls and seven "
