                          "All her people sigh.\n"
                          "They seek bread.\n"
                          "They have given their pleasant things for food to "
                          "refresh their soul.\n"
                          "'Look, Yahweh, and see;\n"
                          "for I have become despised.'\n"
                          "'Is it nothing to you, all you who pass by?\n"
                          "Look, and see if there is any sorrow like my "
                          "sorrow,\n"
                          "which is brought on me,\n"
                          "with which Yahweh has afflicted me in the day of "
                          "his fierce anger.\n"
                          "'From on high has he sent fire into my bones,\n"
                          "and it prevails against them.\n"
                          "He has spread a net for my feet.\n"
                          "He has turned me back.\n"
                          "He has made me desolate and I faint all day long.\n"
                          "'The yoke of my transgressions is bound by his "
